CONTEXT
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Multi-turn flow currently doesn't work because the workflow has no
checkpointer — pending_mrr_data is lost between the upload and the
confirm turns.

TEMPORARY FIX: collapse upload+confirm into one turn. After
excel_handler_node successfully validates, route directly to
mrr_submission_node, which inserts the DB row, then to
auto_verifier_node. User sees the validated summary AND the
submission confirmation in one response.

When SqliteSaver is added later (Task 4.10), we revert this change:
excel_handler_node will once again route to END (waiting for the
user's confirm/cancel turn), restoring the two-turn UX.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SCOPE — graph.py changes only
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Currently the MRR graph has these edges (post-Task 4.7):

  excel_handler -> END
  submit_mrr -> auto_verifier_node
  cancel_mrr -> END

Change to:

  excel_handler -> conditional_router (new): decides between submit_mrr
                   (if validation passed) or END (if validation failed)
  submit_mrr -> auto_verifier_node  (unchanged)
  cancel_mrr -> END  (unchanged — kept for future use)

The new conditional router after excel_handler is needed because
mrr_submission_node should only run if validation actually populated
pending_mrr_data. If validation failed (and pending_mrr_data is None),
we end without inserting anything.

──── Concrete changes ────

(a) Add a small router function inside graph.py (or in nodes.py if
    that's cleaner — your call). Suggest defining inline in graph.py
    next to the existing add_conditional_edges definitions:

    def excel_handler_post_router(state: MaterialRequisitionState) -> str:
        """
        After excel_handler runs, decide whether to auto-submit.
        TEMPORARY: bypasses the confirm/cancel turn because no
        checkpointer exists. Will be removed when SqliteSaver lands
        (Task 4.10).
        """
        pending = state.get("pending_mrr_data")
        if pending and pending.get("valid"):
            return "auto_submit"
        return "end"

(b) Change the edge for excel_handler:

